@jimschubert we use this for loop to find out the name of the name of the composedSchema and we use it below to check that one of the oneOf models is an extracted inline schema.
This for loop is needed because the Schema.name is null for all schemas in allSchemas and in composedSchema.
Do you want me to edit the getSchemas method to set the names in the returned schemas? Then I could Use composedSchema.getName() like you have described.
However, that may have widespread impacts because comparing two schemas would then give different results if one had the name and one didn't have it.
For reference:
    public static Map<String, Schema> getSchemas(OpenAPI openAPI) {
        if (openAPI != null && openAPI.getComponents() != null && openAPI.getComponents().getSchemas() != null) {
            return openAPI.getComponents().getSchemas();
        }
        return Collections.emptyMap();
    }

When we return openAPI.getComponents().getSchemas() none of those schemas have name set in them.
